shrink: A conventional Rails application managing the described behaviour of an application.

Database info:
1.  Install postgreSQL

2.  Configure UTF8 encoding
* Change template1 template database via:
---------------- Taken from: http://www.postgresql.org/docs/8.1/interactive/manage-ag-templatedbs.html -----------------
-- Connect as the postgres superuser, e.g.:
-- psql -U postgres template1
-- Then run:
UPDATE pg_database SET datallowconn = TRUE where datname = 'template0';
\c template0
UPDATE pg_database SET datistemplate = FALSE where datname = 'template1';
drop database template1;
create database template1 with template = template0 encoding = 'UNICODE';
UPDATE pg_database SET datistemplate = TRUE where datname = 'template1';
\c template1
UPDATE pg_database SET datallowconn = FALSE where datname = 'template0';

3. Create users
createuser --createdb --pwprompt shrink_dev
createuser --createdb --pwprompt shrink_test

Password matches username in both cases

4. Create development database
createdb --owner=shrink_dev shrink_dev

4. rake db:reset_and_prepare
